 "components": {
  "instruction": "You will be given a text input that represents a user's natural language utterance. Your task is to classify this utterance into one of a fixed set of intent categories provided below. Your response should be the single best-fitting label from the list; do not include explanations or multiple labels.\n\nThe intent categories are as follows:\n- alarm_query\n- alarm_set\n- calendar_query\n- calendar_remove\n- calendar_set\n- cooking_recipe\n- datetime_query\n- email_query\n- email_sendemail\n- general_quirky\n- iot_hue_lightoff\n- lists_createoradd\n- lists_query\n- lists_remove\n- music_query\n- news_query\n- play_audiobook\n- play_music\n- play_podcasts\n- play_radio\n- qa_currency\n- qa_definition\n- qa_factoid\n- qa_stock\n- recommendation_events\n- recommendation_locations\n- social_post\n- takeaway_order\n- transport_query\n- weather_query\n\nPlease follow these detailed guidelines:\n\n1. **Understand intent definitions:**\n   - \"set\" = The user wants to create, add, or update an item (e.g., setting or creating an alarm, event, list item).\n   - \"query\" = The user seeks to retrieve or check information about an item or status (e.g., checking the weather, looking up an event, retrieving alarms).\n   - \"remove\" = The user wants to delete or clear an item (e.g., removing an event or list item).\n   - \"email_query\" = Checking for, searching, or reading emails. Not for sending emails.\n   - \"email_sendemail\" = Composing and sending an email message.\n   - \"qa_*\" = Seeking factual answers, definitions, currency/conversions, or specific knowledge (e.g., stock prices).\n   - \"play_*\", \"music_query\" = Requests to play or access media content, including music, audiobooks, podcasts, or radio.\n   - \"news_query\" = Requests about current events, news headlines, or what's happening (e.g., \"What has Trump done now?\" should be \"news_query\" not \"qa_factoid\").\n   - \"general_quirky\" = Playful, joke, or non-standard interaction requests.\n   - All other intents should be matched using their definitions above and the closest contextual fit.\n\n2. **Pay close attention to similar or overlapping categories:**\n   - Differentiate between \"set\", \"query\", and \"remove\" by what the user is asking to do with the item (e.g., \"add\" vs \"check\" vs \"delete\").\n   - Distinguish between news topics (for \"news_query\") and general knowledge (\"qa_factoid\"). Political or timely public figure questions generally belong to \"news_query\".\n   - For requests to send emails, always pick \"email_sendemail\"; for checking or searching email, use \"email_query\".\n\n3. **Instructions for output:**\n   - Respond with one and only one category label from the provided list.\n   - Do not provide explanations or any additional text.\n\n4. **Task inputs and format:**\n   - Input will be provided in the format:\n     ```\n     text\n     [user's utterance]\n     ```\n   - Your response should be the label alone.\n\nBy following these instructions, you will help to ensure high-quality, precisely classified intent data. If context or terms seem ambiguous, select the category that best fits the core user action or information requested."
 },
